<subSubSection id="7E3436DC8E79994150EDCCFDBC3175A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B1A49B05D42AA8215F8E3D74133F01CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B86EC74590980E8034FF0B9F44C93AAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
Referring to the host genus, 
<taxonomicName id="FA97E95A044064256DCEB7C0EA0FED88" authority="Mulsant, 1846" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1846" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Halyzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halyzia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AB8CF755ECD5C7C354EB81F261481300" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Halyzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31176A8CB71B041A2517B3D829F7D1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="87A988A427BE3EE75CB75D0E1DEDA578" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="42DD6AE0637BC0941E40008187E5581F" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
Morphologically very similar to other taxa within 
<taxonomicName id="C28CF2CE9C78BD71CD57FB5FF20E80EB" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="8F39CEAF4FF6D06AB54213646F968FA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu lato, but forming a distinct species supported by ITS data. The ITS sequence shares 95.8-97.9% identity with 
<taxonomicName id="DD8EBD5E702543A827DEA92ACAEB12BD" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="E814A9FED93A86586ACBDEB3B9F666FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. from 
<taxonomicName id="1C5EE95EC47847D025F3AA9624744BB7" baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1773" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Harmonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Harmonia axyridis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="axyridis">
<emphasis id="300D12456FD850CDCED41CD0CE26B3C0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Harmonia axyridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 96.5-95.4% with 
<taxonomicName id="7C6F9C61E3DC645CB89558363C4F9941" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="6D7999326E6D4F6C0DC0DE38D97D8392" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. from 
<taxonomicName id="34F66CB2B9080C8209631401668AB9EB" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Adalia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adalia bipunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis id="6BB031E791939F58D8908BE01CDF7C0F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Adalia bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="AC741C793BE0F474F7544D1F26A32F42" genus="A." lsidName="A. decempunctata" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="decempunctata">
<emphasis id="185D98E4727D1E280555A3C22F899362" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">A. decempunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unique molecular synapomorphies in the ITS at positions 478, 517, 652.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
