<subSubSection id="78ACA30BE44E4FC207C040A4995D3319" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="38AEA35DB8B06B5BCA819AEA59364928" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Hosts and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="991498D4E5186BA62BC74FDF5B462BD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
On 
<taxonomicName id="03F070658A138323C558C973116734CD" authority="Mulsant, 1846" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1846" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Halyzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halyzia sedecimguttata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis id="A63CF8F056A8748FEF1EFB41E460B5B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Halyzia sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Belgium and the Netherlands. Previously reported as 
<taxonomicName id="5E9DF9F55954C407CDD1AAB65B50B107" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="060791E0F7604F66D2A05DBB2FB51B8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="033D39A11A3CA2072DD4E72B2EB977DE" author="Haelewaters, D" editor="Peeters, T" journalOrPublisher="Verslag 2015, 21 e onderzoeksjaar. TWM Gronden BV, Tilburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="9 - 12" refId="B50" refString="Haelewaters, D, van Wielink, P, 2016. Hesperomyces virescens (Laboulbeniales) op een nieuwe gastheer. In: Peeters, T, Cramer, T, van Eck, A, Eds., Natuurstudie in De Kaaistoep. Verslag 2015, 21e onderzoeksjaar. TWM Gronden BV, Tilburg: 9 - 12" title="Hesperomyces virescens (Laboulbeniales) op een nieuwe gastheer." volumeTitle="Natuurstudie in De Kaaistoep." year="2016">Haelewaters and van Wielink 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0652D69FD91EFFB24E4A0BB1B19F6E87" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10526-016-9766-8" author="Haelewaters, D" journalOrPublisher="BioControl" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="355 - 371" refId="B53" refString="Haelewaters, D, Zhao, SY, Clusella-Trullas, S, Cottrell, TE, De Kesel, A, Fiedler, L, Herz, A, Hesketh, H, Hui, C, Kleespies, RG, Losey, JE, Minnaar, IA, Murray, KM, Nedved, O, Pfliegler, WP, Raak-van den Berg, CL, Riddick, EW, Shapiro-Ilan, DI, Smyth, RR, Steenberg, T, van Wielink, PS, Viglasova, S, Zhao, Z, Ceryngier, P, Roy, HE, 2017. Parasites of Harmonia axyridis: current research and perspectives. BioControl 62: 355 - 371, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s10526-016-9766-8" title="Parasites of Harmonia axyridis: current research and perspectives." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10526-016-9766-8" volume="62" year="2017">Haelewaters et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="0ED78AE6F93E968306A9FB7E331EA987" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="FEF50DF72B4EA7020B1ADA6C84261AA3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu lato (
<bibRefCitation id="04A472004729A4CE804804BEA11C6A69" author="De Kesel, A" journalOrPublisher="Sterbeeckia" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="3 - 143" refId="B23" refString="De Kesel, A, Gerstmans, C, Haelewaters, D, 2020. Catalogue of the Laboulbeniomycetes of Belgium. Sterbeeckia 36: 3 - 143" title="Catalogue of the Laboulbeniomycetes of Belgium." volume="36" year="2020">De Kesel et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). One unverified record is available from France (
<bibRefCitation id="6DEAC356D19996E15035E77628E7115E" author="Justamond, M" journalOrPublisher="Karstenia" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" publicationUrl="https://www.flickr.com/photos/rock_wolf/49500355673/" refId="B58" refString="Justamond, M, 2019. Halyzia 16-guttata. https://www.flickr.com/photos/rock_wolf/49500355673/" title="Halyzia 16 - guttata." url="https://www.flickr.com/photos/rock_wolf/49500355673/" year="2019">Justamond 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D23A7FEB1F104184D2C7DE1B91544640" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="notes">
<paragraph id="000AAE9293BF7974EEC4B9FFC50EAF07" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A28930AB173E250DE4DB4B56204BFD43" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
Supported by multi-locus phylogenetic analyses and sequence-based species delimitation methods, 
<bibRefCitation id="26F04D0037D4FBABDA6BD0BDBD1EE387" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-34319-5" author="Haelewaters, D" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" refId="B44" refString="Haelewaters, D, De Kesel, A, Pfister, DH, 2018. Integrative taxonomy reveals hidden species within a common fungal parasite of ladybirds. Scientific Reports 8: 15966. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-34319-5" title="Integrative taxonomy reveals hidden species within a common fungal parasite of ladybirds. Scientific Reports 8: 15966." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-34319-5" year="2018">Haelewaters et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName id="8A0B511BF1DF7006A5705392AF0187FA" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="90574898D80930D5E73C95983CFFB9EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thaxt. is a complex of multiple species, segregated by host. The authors proposed to &quot;restrict 
<taxonomicName id="98ADEE13915D894B1F5597762985004F" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="4BAD56B796EFF9515E383B9B1A8216FE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu stricto to those thalli found on 
<taxonomicName id="3D3DA050ED42B5551FAB60E3A671BDD5" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Chilocorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chilocorus stigma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigma">
<emphasis id="FE6694509EA8B5FD25F8FA5A00815ECB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Chilocorus stigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the host species on which the fungus was originally described&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="E9656505F359B41E67075D3F392BFDB4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/20020441" author="Thaxter, R" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="261 - 270" refId="B109" refString="Thaxter, R, 1891. Supplementary note on North American Laboulbeniaceae. Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences 25: 261 - 270, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/20020441" title="Supplementary note on North American Laboulbeniaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/20020441" volume="25" year="1891">Thaxter 1891</bibRefCitation>
). Here, we included two isolates from 
<taxonomicName id="2570E1952884C5D6C9D338731EAA78B5" genus="C." lsidName="C. stigma" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="stigma">
<emphasis id="F3EE5E31D519BBE88E706AE1C1F3C7C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">C. stigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Say, 1835), and found the clade representative of 
<taxonomicName id="77FDFFFF430C9C8EDEB5359C69ADDA06" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="C328FB85798E2972FAD346D1374F0956" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu stricto. Based on this analysis and previous work (
<bibRefCitation id="6BE06878720F41073EAC5FF95EA52968" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-34319-5" author="Haelewaters, D" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" refId="B44" refString="Haelewaters, D, De Kesel, A, Pfister, DH, 2018. Integrative taxonomy reveals hidden species within a common fungal parasite of ladybirds. Scientific Reports 8: 15966. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-34319-5" title="Integrative taxonomy reveals hidden species within a common fungal parasite of ladybirds. Scientific Reports 8: 15966." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-34319-5" year="2018">Haelewaters et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), we can start describing the individual clades as distinct species. A monographic work with formal descriptions for the seven other species within 
<taxonomicName id="9CA42F2A3220303A215C06F8A4E613DD" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="15ED571BA186C8E01475214A6EF8FA85" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. is in preparation, but in the light of this checklist we decided to describe 
<taxonomicName id="98BFCFB92CBB2F113214C878A641EE7F" genus="H." lsidName="H. halyziae" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="halyziae">
<emphasis id="1EEDE3DEAE470D83A50684D60079FCB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. halyziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was only known from a single collection in the Netherlands until we recently collected it in Belgium (Mar.-Apr. 2019).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF0FBF2F447E998E046D95FAD3D40589" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<bibRefCitation id="90D7A132E8DFA74C5D53F4A1291C94F5" author="Haelewaters, D" editor="Peeters, T" journalOrPublisher="Verslag 2015, 21 e onderzoeksjaar. TWM Gronden BV, Tilburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="9 - 12" refId="B50" refString="Haelewaters, D, van Wielink, P, 2016. Hesperomyces virescens (Laboulbeniales) op een nieuwe gastheer. In: Peeters, T, Cramer, T, van Eck, A, Eds., Natuurstudie in De Kaaistoep. Verslag 2015, 21e onderzoeksjaar. TWM Gronden BV, Tilburg: 9 - 12" title="Hesperomyces virescens (Laboulbeniales) op een nieuwe gastheer." volumeTitle="Natuurstudie in De Kaaistoep." year="2016">Haelewaters and van Wielink (2016)</bibRefCitation>
reported an infected specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="C9566D4BF5FC3BF1FD75C5FEEF653F03" authority="Mulsant, 1846" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1846" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Halyzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halyzia sedecimguttata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis id="8110A08325E1EE0A54D7C815D1A577A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Halyzia sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from nature reserve De Kaaistoep in the Netherlands. In 1997-2015, 476 individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="478EA3926D7B0C80871B5E41BA6417FF" genus="H." lsidName="H. sedecimguttata" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis id="91BE164E1F777B98BCC7D36779215002" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected on a lighted white sheet and screened for presence of 
<taxonomicName id="ED17DAAFBC1744D1C0BC3EC46EB472F0" genus="H." lsidName="" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="order">Laboulbeniales</taxonomicName>
, only resulting in one individual (parasite prevalence 0.2%). In Belgium, a population of infected 
<taxonomicName id="42A1FED85B2027A8B4A91DD32069BE91" genus="H." lsidName="H. sedecimguttata" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis id="67491027F7E380538A415E75C34B9F75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found at the Meise Botanic Garden. Specimens were collected in spring 2019 while they were leaving their overwintering place-deep cracks in the woodwork of a small forest chapel. Screening of 46 specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="9C51AA19FEFDF2C419DC2FF8B7B7B57F" genus="H." lsidName="H. sedecimguttata" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis id="CF0B2F66E6847B3B49A1366ECB03EACB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed nine infected ones (parasite prevalence 19.5%). This ladybird species seems to overwinter singly or in small congregations in narrow overwintering places, including in leaf litter, under foliage on stone walls, on trunks and branches (
<bibRefCitation id="2C89B4A7730F0B7E241DD7F180C1051E" author="Majerus, MEN" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Gazette" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="71 - 78" refId="B67" refString="Majerus, MEN, Williams, Z, 1989. The distribution and life history of the orange ladybird, Halyzia sedecimguttata (L.) (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) in Britain. Entomologist's Gazette 40: 71 - 78" title="The distribution and life history of the orange ladybird, Halyzia sedecimguttata (L.) (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) in Britain." volume="40" year="1989">Majerus and Williams 1989</bibRefCitation>
). This congregation behavior is beneficial for transmission of the fungus and is also observed in 
<taxonomicName id="5F2D44BFFC0EE26CAE4B8A0F06EFAF7B" baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1773" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Harmonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Harmonia axyridis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="axyridis">
<emphasis id="4EC0B3ACDE9E64912DBD5D2B4D5D0316" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Harmonia axyridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F8B633FE942CA3FAFE11A7AEA6FDDC69" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10526-016-9766-8" author="Haelewaters, D" journalOrPublisher="BioControl" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="355 - 371" refId="B53" refString="Haelewaters, D, Zhao, SY, Clusella-Trullas, S, Cottrell, TE, De Kesel, A, Fiedler, L, Herz, A, Hesketh, H, Hui, C, Kleespies, RG, Losey, JE, Minnaar, IA, Murray, KM, Nedved, O, Pfliegler, WP, Raak-van den Berg, CL, Riddick, EW, Shapiro-Ilan, DI, Smyth, RR, Steenberg, T, van Wielink, PS, Viglasova, S, Zhao, Z, Ceryngier, P, Roy, HE, 2017. Parasites of Harmonia axyridis: current research and perspectives. BioControl 62: 355 - 371, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s10526-016-9766-8" title="Parasites of Harmonia axyridis: current research and perspectives." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10526-016-9766-8" volume="62" year="2017">Haelewaters et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9249545548AEF0FD2FFA7EB5797CC77E" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="1D59CE61F712D95BDC2E23CA086C70C4" genus="H." lsidName="H. halyziae" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="halyziae">
<emphasis id="7AE9B695F86D04228D053F74EC2735E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. halyziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to what we have thus far accepted as 
<taxonomicName id="A3925E5BA60E9938412761C9C9D1241D" genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="CC9D796B8FF78E2C40E413D6DFFC80CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Within the Kingdom 
<taxonomicName id="4E7DFBCDE7C41CE189AD370B6F0AEF5D" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="kingdom">Fungi</taxonomicName>
, there is an incredible diversity that cannot be perceived through morphology. Cryptic species are being uncovered in 
<taxonomicName id="E352257FBB264ED14B0945186D167F4D" class="Agaricomycetes" genus="H." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="class">Agaricomycetes</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="E4F0E981ABCAD938F9BE5B06E8C000CA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2013.10.019" author="Stefani, FOP" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="249 - 260" refId="B104" refString="Stefani, FOP, Jones, RH, May, TW, 2014. Concordance of seven gene genealogies compared to phenotypic data reveals multiple cryptic species in Australian dermocyboid Cortinarius (Agaricales). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 71: 249 - 260, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2013.10.019" title="Concordance of seven gene genealogies compared to phenotypic data reveals multiple cryptic species in Australian dermocyboid Cortinarius (Agaricales)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2013.10.019" volume="71" year="2014">Stefani et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5EA7BEB240668731D7CCE90163C502E8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funbio.2016.08.005" author="Sanchez-Garcia, M" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="1540 - 1553" refId="B92" refString="Sanchez-Garcia, M, Henkel, TW, Aime, MC, Smith, ME, Matheny, PB, 2016. Guyanagarika, a new ectomycorrhizal genus of Agaricales from the Neotropics. Fungal Biology 120: 1540 - 1553, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funbio.2016.08.005" title="Guyanagarika, a new ectomycorrhizal genus of Agaricales from the Neotropics." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funbio.2016.08.005" volume="120" year="2016">
<normalizedToken id="66168F94604BC3E290845CDE7B915B6E" originalValue="Sánchez-García">Sanchez-Garcia</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="2CA322AD491CF0E227395BA085695604" class="Lecanoromycetes" genus="H." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="class">Lecanoromycetes</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="2E146B863B003383F5E5589FCF4599B3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0124625" author="Singh, G" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" refId="B101" refString="Singh, G, Dal Grande, F, Divakar, PK, Otte, J, Leavitt, SD, Szczepanska, K, Crespo, A, Rico, VJ, Aptroot, A, da Silva Caceres, ME, Lumbsch, HT, Schmitt, I, 2015. Coalescentbased species delimitation approach uncovers high cryptic diversity in the cosmopolitan lichen-forming fungal genus Protoparmelia (Lecanorales, Ascomycota). PloS ONE 10: e0124625. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0124625" title="Coalescentbased species delimitation approach uncovers high cryptic diversity in the cosmopolitan lichen-forming fungal genus Protoparmelia (Lecanorales, Ascomycota). PloS ONE 10: e 0124625." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0124625" year="2015">Singh et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), Leotiomyces (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="196B3D9739A9EDB6DBD7F724B6855FED" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.100.1.47" author="Gruenig, CR" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="47 - 67" refId="B37" refString="Gruenig, CR, Duo, A, Sieber, TN, Holdenrieder, O, 2008. Assignment of species rank to six reproductively isolated cryptic species of the Phialocephala fortinii s.l.- Acephala applanata species complex. Mycologia 100: 47 - 67, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.100.1.47" title="Assignment of species rank to six reproductively isolated cryptic species of the Phialocephala fortinii s. l. - Acephala applanata species complex." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.100.1.47" volume="100" year="2008">
<normalizedToken id="1B82443FC4B7D12330D5474200EF791C" originalValue="Grünig">Gruenig</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="E8A4324CB4C4B99BBD7990C3D0745EFF" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="H." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="class">Pucciniomycetes</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="20093D06CAF89B63A6D2691F533501C0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/10-289" author="Bennett, C" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="1004 - 1018" refId="B6" refString="Bennett, C, Aime, MC, Newcombe, G, 2011. Molecular and pathogenic variation within Melampsora on Salix in western North America reveals numerous cryptic species. Mycologia 103: 1004 - 1018, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/10-289" title="Molecular and pathogenic variation within Melampsora on Salix in western North America reveals numerous cryptic species." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/10-289" volume="103" year="2011">Bennett et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="A153E665BEBD5D314D7CFD77D841C9B7" class="Ustilaginomycetes" genus="H." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="class">Ustilaginomycetes</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="A76471589B3586F495B035EC010A37BC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep43549" author="Li, YM" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 13" refId="B64" refString="Li, YM, Shivas, RG, Cai, L, 2017. Cryptic diversity in Tranzscheliella spp. (Ustilaginales) is driven by host switches. Scientific Reports 7: 1 - 13, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep43549" title="Cryptic diversity in Tranzscheliella spp. (Ustilaginales) is driven by host switches." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep43549" volume="7" year="2017">Li et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
), and other major clades. And while the 
<taxonomicName id="384B7D3D048ABCC28B8BECC5D862B640" genus="H." lsidName="" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="order">Laboulbeniales</taxonomicName>
has been the subject of a large-scale study to estimate the global species richness of the group (
<bibRefCitation id="0D6C5D58F85B670AE60C867D0FE7A5EF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1018318320019" author="Weir, A" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity and Conservation" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="701 - 719" refId="B125" refString="Weir, A, Hammond, PM, 1997. Laboulbeniales on beetles: host utilization patterns and species richness of the parasites. Biodiversity and Conservation 6: 701 - 719, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1018318320019" title="Laboulbeniales on beetles: host utilization patterns and species richness of the parasites." url="https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1018318320019" volume="6" year="1997">Weir and Hammond 1997</bibRefCitation>
), cryptic diversity was not part of the equation. In other words, the number of estimated species of 
<taxonomicName id="D1BF97C8355DC2871169D289F362752B" genus="H." lsidName="" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="order">Laboulbeniales</taxonomicName>
, between 15,000 and 75,000, is likely to be corrected to include cryptic species. We note that the recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="42CFC62DB56637DF4D11AABF71995E23" genus="H." lsidName="H. halyziae" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="halyziae">
<emphasis id="1B80E987CA7C8BC454856D062FF54B17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. halyziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only possible through molecular data and host association. Our current understanding is that, within this species complex, there is a strict parasite-host association, with one parasite found only on one host. We think that this host specificity exists at the genus level, given the 
<taxonomicName id="46C11416579F3590E07116002E1ED649" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Adalia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4051690397A37BCF9B0EF647FCA106D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Adalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (Figure 
<figureCitation id="F984CFB2195445FA14F5EB0935CE3AB4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum clade creditability tree of Hesperomyces isolates reconstructed from an ITS dataset, with H. coleomegillae as outgroup. The topology is the result of Bayesian inference performed with BEAST. For each node, ML BS (≥ 65) and Bayesian pp (≥ 0.7) are presented above / below the branch leading to that node. Hesperomyces virescens sensu lato is highlighted with light gray shading, isolates are color-coded by host; H. virescens sensu stricto and H. halyziae sp. nov. are highlighted with dark gray shading." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.71.53421.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/437751" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">1</figureCitation>
), which includes isolates from thalli removed from two host species within the same genus.
</paragraph>
